{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016DySegdnvRrhKi8UQs2yr2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture:\n\n1. The Prometheus deployment is listening on port 9090, but the Service exposes it on port 8000 (mapped to 9090).\n2. The Prometheus configmap only has a scrape config for `localhost:9090` (self-scraping) - it's missing the RabbitMQ scrape configuration.\n3. The `rules.yml` is present in the configmap but it's not being loaded by Prometheus (no `--rules-files` arg in the deployment).\n4. RabbitMQ metrics are available on port 15692 with `/metrics`.\n5. There's a headless service `rabbitmq-headless` with port 15692 exposed.\n\nTo fix this, I need to update the Prometheus configmap to add a scrape job for RabbitMQ targeting all 3 pods individually using their headless service DNS names so they appear as separate targets in Prometheus.\n\nI also need to ensure Prometheus loads the rules file by adding a `rule_files` section in prometheus.yml that references rules.yml. Looking at the service configuration, there's a port mapping where the Prometheus service exposes port 8000 but the container listens on 9090, which is fine since the service handles the translation. I need to update the ConfigMap with the RabbitMQ scrape configuration using the headless service DNS names for each pod, and then reload Prometheus through the lifecycle endpoint since it's enabled.\n\nWriting scrape config...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1243,"cache_read_input_tokens":30012,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1243},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bd9c460b-92ad-4a19-908f-14ad453bad3f","uuid":"bba124a3-7c8a-404c-a2bd-0b02c8c36b3c","request_id":"req_011Ccd3zvPsfDzjPMp5huPWm"}
